Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life is the time of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.37,0:00:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.27,0:00:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ketsudan (decision)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.27,0:00:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom Use your head Keep thinking it you're a man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you cry or laugh, it depends on your decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant even if you win Don't cry even if you lose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.06,0:01:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not show tears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.58,0:01:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.07,0:01:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The US Navy, which has won the Battle of Midway and gained momentum, was about to launch a counterattack against
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.56,0:01:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese in order to take control of the Pacific War.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.94,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On August 6th, 1942, a fleet of 31 ships carrying 19,000 Marines was secretly heading north into the South Pacific,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.01,0:02:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,protected by approximately 60 escort ships centered on three aircraft carriers and one battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Savo Island (Episode 13)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.80,0:02:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the Tulagi and Guadalcanal campaigns is primarily to enable contact between the United States and Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.70,0:02:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, it was a stepping stone to control Rabaul. Third, it would prevent the Japanese troops from moving further south.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.45,0:02:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the reconnaissance aircraft reports, no planes have yet arrived at the Japanese airfield under construction at Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.94,0:02:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, they can come from Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.18,0:02:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> For that purpose, there is a coast watcher of the Royal Australian Navy Intelligence Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.80,0:02:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> These coast watchers are farmers, pastors, officials, miners, etc. who were mobilized to protect the vast Australian coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:03:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They lurked in the jungle with the local people, and were in charge of informing every movement of the Japanese army .
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.63,0:03:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> The distance from Rabaul to Tulagi and Guadalcanal is about 560 nautical miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy can only fly over us for 20 or 30 minutes at the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.94,0:03:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, it will take at least four days for our army to complete the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.66,0:03:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the enemy makes an attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.25,0:03:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,> We have already lost Lexington in the Coral Sea and Yorktown at Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.42,0:03:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we lose more aircraft carriers? Aircraft carriers are vulnerable to bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.39,0:03:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,> As the landing commander, I cannot kill 20,000 Marines. I need the support of an aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.35,0:03:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,> I'm not just saying that as a commander of the aircraft carrier fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.70,0:04:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If two of the three remaining aircraft carriers in the Pacific, or even one, are killed, the war is lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.42,0:04:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,> Then, you should cancel such an operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.04,0:04:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> Tell General Nimitz or Vice Admiral Ghormley in Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.87,0:04:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Well, don't get so excited. The operation has already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.87,0:04:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> Anyway, why don't you carry out the landing operation as planned and then reconsider after seeing the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,> Are you scared? > Are you not seared?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,> I try not to think about the future. > We are not Tarzan. Can you fight these guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.59,0:04:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> Japanese soldiers can dive for miles while sucking air from trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.52,0:05:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Barefoot, no noise in the jungle, climbs trees like a monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Evil, ascetic, and able to travel farther than we do. They can survive with a small amount of food and endure any pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.49,0:05:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,> I'm really scared too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.45,0:05:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,> They are not ordinary human beings. They are werewolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.59,0:05:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,> On August 7th, at 3:00 am, the American transport fleet approaching Cape Esperance, northwest of Guadalcanal Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.01,0:05:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,split into two parts across Savo Island at the entrance of the narrow strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Protected by the escort fleet, and Guadalcanal Island. They approached Cape Lunga and Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.14,0:05:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, on Guadalcanal Island, the construction of an airfield for the Japanese army had been completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.47,0:06:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> Today, the 6th Air Group, Misawa Air Group, and Mitsubishi G4M Corps are scheduled to fly from Rabaul to this Guadalcanal airfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, the airfield construction team will conduct pilot training, Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes > Good. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.95,0:06:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> At this time, the Japanese defense force of Guadalcanal was about 2000 members of the construction team
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and 203 members of the Japanese land squadron. And there were 700 Japanese troops in Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.54,0:06:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The US-Australian fleet attacked seaplane bases on Guadalcanal and Tulagi on Florida, and began landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.95,0:06:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Headquarters predicted that the US military would rebound in the latter half of 1943, given its military strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.61,0:06:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the counterattack was faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.61,0:07:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Rabaul air base on the Japanese side that received this news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> Immediately raise all troops and attack the invading enemy units.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.51,0:07:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,> I think the enemy's intention is a reconnaissance in force or the destruction of the airfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.54,0:07:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,> 2nd unit, 27 Mitsubish G4Ms, 1st unit, 18 Zero fighters for 07:30, 3rd unit, 9 aircraft, start as soon as ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,> Also, after the Battle of Midway, the 8th Fleet, the combined fleet under the command of Vice Admiral Mikawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.89,0:07:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was about to head to Guadalcanal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.51,0:08:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> The distance from Rabaul to Guadalcanal is just about Shimonoseki from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.26,0:08:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot expect much success from our military airplanes. > However, our fleet has just been formed and has not yet take any fleet action.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, since it is such a distance, there is a good chance that it will be attacked by enemy aircraft on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.30,0:08:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm prepared for that too. Since the battle of Midway, our navy has been too cowardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.78,0:08:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> What is the opinion of Chief Yamamoto? > He agrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.99,0:08:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,> I will do so with the free discretion given to the fleet, even if opposed by the Imperial Headquarters or the Combined Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.40,0:08:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,> Chief, let's do it. > How about you, Chief of Staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.99,0:08:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> If the chief is so determined, then I will not dissent. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.06,0:08:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.47,0:09:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> Decide what to do later based on the result of the land based air reconnaissance and attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.09,0:09:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,> Good. Senior Staff? > We have never sailed the surface of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.92,0:09:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> Anyway, it's a rough strategy, so there is no choice but to make it rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.37,0:09:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,> Alright, this is the first fleet night battle in the history of this world war. Let's do it roughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The flagship, and the 6th Fleet, will sortie immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.54,0:09:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,> for the Japanese side, being deprived of Guadalcanal would be a serious threat to the New Guinea area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> 24 bombers, head toward Tuvalu and Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,> This information was sent to the headquarters of the Hawaii Pacific Fleet, and was forwarded to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the US operational unit sailing near Guadalcanal Island by strong radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.30,0:10:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> The ship is scheduled to be attacked by 24 enemy aircraft at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,> The upper right sky, enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.54,0:11:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,> Good
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.40,0:11:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,> The damage suffered by the Japanese side in this battle was five land based attack aircraft five shipboard bombers, and two Zero fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.26,0:11:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The damage to the US and Australian army was 11 fighters, one dive bomber, and the destroyer McMurdo was sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,> The problem is the enemy aircraft carrier. > Therefore, we have to be prepared for an invasion of enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.16,0:12:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,> If that happens, and there is no aircraft carrier here, then we may be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.99,0:12:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be discovered by the enemy at all costs. The only thing that will beat the enemy is a surprise attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.47,0:12:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,> Right front, enemy patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,> Alright, pretend to head northwest. > Full port. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,> Enemy patrol aircraft has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,> Restore our course. The rest of you gather in the operation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.09,0:13:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.02,0:13:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,> We passed through the Bougainville Strait and broke through the central waterway at high speed. Rush from the right side of Savo Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.57,0:13:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,First, a surprise attack will be made to the ships moored in Guadalcanal, then the enemy of Tulagi will be attacked,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.92,0:13:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the enemy planes will hurry back to a point where they cannot be attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.95,0:13:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,> Enemy patrol aircraft, 90 degrees to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.30,0:13:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,> Cruisers three, destroyers three,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.28,0:14:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,seaplane tenders two, course 120 degrees, speed 15 knots,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.90,0:14:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> Persistent guy. Would you like to change direction again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,> It takes too much time. Don't worry, threaten them with an 8-inch gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.83,0:14:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> With this, there is no doubt that enemy planes will come in a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,> Start each aircraft and scout the enemy's condition. Each ship should have a strict anti-aircraft lookout.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, the reconnaissance officer belonging to the Royal Australian Air Force,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who discovered the Japanese fleet, continued to scout the area they were charged with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.70,0:15:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At around 2:30 pm, they returned to their base in Milne Bay, on the southern tip of New Guinea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.70,0:15:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They then reported the formation of the Japanese fleet, unconfirmed to MacArthur's Command in Townsville, Australia. It's a delay of nearly 8 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.66,0:16:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,> Apparently we are okay. > I have never had a day was as long as today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.49,0:16:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,> We will surely win tonight. > Good. I'm giving instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.07,0:16:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.56,0:16:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,> Instruction: Win and rush into the night battle, Which is a tradition of the Imperial Japanese Navy. Be calm and do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.21,0:16:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,> Call Admiral Ghormley.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.32,0:17:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,> We have finished the mission of landing support, 21 out of 99 carrier-based aircraft were lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.14,0:17:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> Due to the large number of enemy bombers and torpedo bombers, it seems appropriate for our fleet to withdraw immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.80,0:17:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There is also a shortage of fuel, so we must request that a refueling ship be dispatched as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> Actually, there was still four days worth of fuel. However, the American side pulled out their escort fleet, including the aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.25,0:17:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral Fletcher decided he didn't want to risk losing his aircraft carrier anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.07,0:17:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,now that he lost Lexington and Yorktown in the two battles of the Coral Sea and Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.46,0:18:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> Report from Aoba's reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.63,0:18:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Three enemy cruisers patrolling Savo Island, and southwestern sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.74,0:18:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, from now on, we will rush to the berth on Guadalcanal Island with a speed of 30 knots and a course of 95 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.01,0:18:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,> 10 degrees to the right, three cruisers. Going to the right. Illumination!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,> Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.46,0:19:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> 10 minutes > It's a major victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.63,0:19:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,> Immediately change course to the left and run the troops off Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.66,0:20:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.97,0:21:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> Currently at 00:10. Feel free to give your opinions. > We should withdraw immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.39,0:21:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There are few torpedoes and an enemy task force is believed to be near San Crisbal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.04,0:21:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> The problem is distance and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.11,0:21:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,> It takes two hours to reorganize the fleet and reach Lunga Point, no matter how urgent it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.66,0:21:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's past 4o'clock, its morning on the Solomon Sea, so
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.39,0:21:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> it is impossible to escape from the enemy aircraft carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.14,0:21:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,> Two hours > Let's do it. The enemy convoy should be naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.59,0:22:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,> The chief also said. If we were discovered by an aircraft carrier, our force would be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.11,0:22:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> Withdraw the entire force. Course 320 degrees. speed 30 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.94,0:22:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, at that time, the American aircraft carrier had left far away from Guadalcanal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> Chief, let's go attack again. If we go only with Chokai, we can escape fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.56,0:22:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you leave the convoy, your enemies will only get fat. Chief, a well supplied enemy will affect future operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.01,0:23:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> We cannot lose an important warship by making a reckless attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.94,0:23:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,> Thus, the first night battle in the history of naval battles in the world ended with a one-sided victory for the Japanese side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.49,0:23:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Guadalcanal’s American convoy was left unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.39,0:23:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Given replenishment of troops, ammunition, and food has a major impact on the final victory, was this decision correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.11,0:23:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When making a decision, always look to the future and not lose sight of the big picture, without hesitation about the immediate victory or damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.42,0:23:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This naval battle, which brought victory to the Japanese side, was one of the major causes of the upcoming tragedy of Guadalcanal. When making a decision, always look to the future and not lose sight of the big picture, without hesitation about the immediate victory or damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.42,0:23:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This naval battle, which brought victory to the Japanese side, was one of the major causes of the upcoming tragedy of Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:24:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.92,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, test your strength It you are a man, burn your hope
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.44,0:24:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you area man, don't let yourself down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I and you are men and men bleed the same bright red blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.51,0:25:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
